dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Digitized at 1:8000. Edges of the floodplain are based on whatever most recent LiDAR is available, and the 10 m DEM where we dont have any LiDAR.

Decisions about how far to follow the tributaries were guided mainly by the upstream accumulation area attributed to the reach in the Stillwater stream data in some combination with the width of the valley. An ad-hoc threshold of 32110000 was set for FROMAREA, just to make sure that all the streams of particular interest to us were included (primarily Iskuulpe Creek). Canals were excluded.

DOGAMI geology map was used to confirm the LiDAR information, reconsider the inclusion of tributaries, and deliniate ambiguous areas of low relief (primarily the meadows on upper Meacham Creek, Wildhorse Creek near Adams, and the Cold Springs area).

This replaces the 1998 effort, which can be found in the GIS archive.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: An outline of the mainstream Umatilla River floodplain.
